         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">LADIES' ¶ LEICHARDT ¶ SEARCH ¶ COMMITTEE ¶ 28/6/65...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">65.06.28</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Branwhite Clarke</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">DL MS Q371, pp. 141-4, W. B. Clarke papers, Dixson Library, State Library of New South Wales.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">The transcription given in Moyal (2003), pp. 708-9, differs from that given here.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times, Times; ">LADIES'</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times, Times; ">LEICHARDT</seg>
               <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Leichhardt's name mis-spelled in the printed letterhead.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times, Times; ">SEARCH</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times, Times; ">COMMITTEE</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">28/6/65</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Reverend and venerable friend,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your letter just arrived is certainly so admirable, that with consent of the Ladies Committe I have the main portion of it transferred to the "Australasian,"<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See W. B. Clarke to M, 20 June 1865.</p>
               </note> trusting that you will not disapprove of the step. It is but just that your noble exertions should be fully known, especially as I have in my speech at St George's Hall<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B65.02.01, subsequently widely reprinted.</p>
               </note> not done justice to you. This apparent shortcoming arose from the fact, that only a few months before I had in the report on the graves found by Conn &amp; Giles, referred to some extent to your exertions &amp; your opinions.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">B65.14.05, a copy of which was sent to Augustus Gregory 'to obtain his opinion as to the further investigation concerning Leichhardt's fate' (resolution at the meeting of the Royal Society of Victoria, 10 October 1864 after M had read the report, </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Transactions and proceedings of the Royal Society of Victoria</seg>
                     <seg style="">, <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>vol. 6, p. lii).</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> The only copy I had of your long printed letter,<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">'Leichhardt and the Desert', <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Sydney morning herald</seg>, 24 August 1858, pp. 4-5.</p>
               </note> in which you weigh so fully the evidence I sent with our report to Mr Gregory &amp; have had no oppurtunity of restoring it. The report is however printed in the new volume of our Royal Society &amp; thus my appreciation of your exertions permanently recorded.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mrs Dr Bromby has secured the cooperation of Prof Pell, a friend of her brother. I trust you will unite with the few, who now uphold conjointly your friend's claims.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sundry articles in the Melbourne papers will show what progress is made. Pardon me for the briefness &amp; inelegance of this note. I write hurriedly amidst other engagements.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>May you enjoy the blessings of health &amp; contentedness, that is the wish of your attached</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd Mueller</p>
         </div>
      </body>
